    <item>
      <title>Hyrule Warriors Weapon Collection</title>
      <author>heavenseyes</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/548408</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/548408#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">7172f1effb861432ee4f7911e97d452e29392a08</guid>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 Oct 2024 02:02:44 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0ec1a814a.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e845b1df.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e844dd12.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e83afe81.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e841f481.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e840f670.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e84b8fa5.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e843beaa.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/670c0e84a8505.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;h1&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Hyrule Warriors Weapon Collection&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u class="SelectedElement"&gt;Weapon Details:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To start, each weapon in this mod is a &lt;u&gt;standalone weapon&lt;/u&gt; as well as an &lt;u&gt;unbreakable weapon&lt;/u&gt;. I tried balancing these weapons stat-wise around the existing weapons in the game as a means to not make them too overpowered. Some weapons don't follow this rule. &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;mainly due to bias&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;Example:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;br&gt;Strongest 1-handed weapon in mod: Link's &lt;b&gt;Magical Sword&lt;/b&gt; (&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Level 3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;)- Attack stat of &lt;b&gt;55&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Strongest 1-handed weapon in game&lt;b&gt;*&lt;/b&gt;:&lt;b&gt; Master Sword&lt;/b&gt; (fully upgraded) - Attack stat of &lt;b&gt;60&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;*&lt;/b&gt;This is using base stats only, not including weapons with bonus traits&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Weapon Locations:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When creating this mod, I tried to see if I could incorporate a form of an upgrade system. Because of this, &lt;b&gt;only the Level 1 versions of each weapon can be found across Hyrule&lt;/b&gt;. Some weapons are rewarded by progressing the game while other weapons require a bit of exploring to find.&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;You can 'upgrade' the Level 1 versions of the weapons into the &lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Level 2&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Level 3&lt;/span&gt; versions of the weapons with Cherry at the Akkala Ancient Tech Lab.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;The &lt;b&gt;'&lt;i&gt;upgrade&lt;/i&gt;'&lt;/b&gt; here means that you must have the &lt;u&gt;previous weapon level&lt;/u&gt; in your inventory in order to purchase the next level.&lt;br&gt;&lt;u&gt;Example&lt;/u&gt;: Link's &lt;b&gt;White Sword&lt;/b&gt; (&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Level 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;) - must have Link's &lt;b&gt;Knight Sword&lt;/b&gt; (&lt;b&gt;Level 1&lt;/b&gt;) in order to purchase.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Warning&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;: The Level 1 weapons &lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;do not respawn&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt; after being obtained. Keep that in mind when upgrading your weapons and managing inventory space (There are more weapons being added than inventory slots available, &lt;b&gt;you will run out of inventory space&lt;/b&gt;)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;"Psst. Rumor has it that a certain person &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;Grante&lt;/span&gt; sells rare items. They may even sell &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;Level 1&lt;/span&gt; weapons. Be careful: &lt;span class="Spoiler"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;"&lt;/i&gt;     -&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Mysterious Traveler&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Weapons List:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Here is the complete list of all the weapons included in this mod. Each weapon will have its level listed and its game origin (Hyrule Warriors - HW or Hyrule Warriors: Age of Calamity - AoC) If you have no interest in searching for these weapons, I will include the location of ea